Zambian Strikes Extend to State-Owned Companies, Times Reports

-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 
2011-10-04T09:16:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/zambian-strikes-extend-to-state-owned-companies-times-reports.html
Hundreds of workers are on strike
over pay at five Zambian companies, including state-owned
entities, the  Times of Zambia  said, citing labor leaders,
government officials and employers.  The companies affected are Zambezi Portland Cement Ltd.,
Zinc Aluminum Copper and Ore Co. and Full Value Goodness Millers
Ltd., the daily reported. Workers at state-owned power utility
Zambia Electricity Supply Corp. Ltd. and Mpulungu port on Lake
Tanganyika staged protests, the Times said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  